rComments: The teacher is actually good. He explains his content properly. However his slides don't have a lot of information as there is a textbook and he expects you to come to class. Not coming to class is at your own risk. He always answers questions, even if the topic you're asking about is old. Even if he has been explaining for 30 minutes, he answers.
Just don't take this professor or you'll regret it!

Avoid at all costs! With this prof you can expect 15-30 minute weekly videos on subjects that should normally take 3 hours to explain. He gives very very few examples and doesn't interact at all with his students. To sum up, you're paying thousands of dollars to teach yourself 3 hours worth of very difficult material entirely by yourself.

This prof was simply horrible. I have an almost perfect CGPA but was only able to obtain a B+ in this class due to the final exam being worth 60% of our final grade and the fact that class was completely a-synchronous (we weren't in a zoom with him ONCE) and he rarely answers emails. If you put in work you can "do good", but avoid if you want A+

J'ai suivi ce cours en ligne du fait de la pandémie. Nous avions une capsule de 30 minutes par semaine à regarder à la place d'un cours de normalement 3 heures. Nous devions nous débrouiller par nous mêmes et le professeur n'était pas là pour nous épauler (aucune interaction). L'examen final (unique examen) ne représente pas la matière des DGDs...
Pretty difficult, but great at explaining the course content. Clear grading criteria and what is in the course is directly in assignments and exam.

Really great prof. Attendance to class is required as there is not much content on the slides; however, if you are present, just sit, listen, and take notes: everything will be as clear as day. Exams are not easy btw, but there are no traps. Study the examples from class a few times and you will be fine.

Tu dois te présenter à tous les cours mais il explique quand même bien la matière et ses tests sont très justes. C'est exactement les exercices qu'il a fait en classe (à quelques twists près pour voir si tu comprend réellement et tu n'as pas juste appris la matière par coeur)
His slides are empty, and if you skip classes, you won't pass.

Not good. Spends WAY too much time explaining theory and how the formulas come about rather than their application. You absolutely need to attend class. Average for the first midterm was 52, with 20% of the class getting under 20%. Final exam is easier. Literally ended class at 9:54. Try to avoid, everyone says the English class is easier.

He's making the class harder than it already is. Half of the class failed his mid-term. I am a student who normally receive A's and in this class I end up having a C+. I strongly recommand to take this class in English even if you're not perfectly bilingual. The only positive part is that his assignments are helpful and reflete the course.

As a student specializing in finance, I was excited to take my first finance class. I am a really good student but this prof made things so complicated. I could not understand his lectures. Almost half of the class failed the midterm and most dropped the class afterward. Final was tough. Retook this class in English and got an A.
I'm a very good student and I normally do very well in school but this prof is a tough grader and he's not very helpfull. Good luck...

Everything in the class seems all clear, you think you did well on the exam and then somehow get a horrible grade, grading criteria are not clear. But overall the teacher is nice and doesn't put hard numbers on the exam.

Complete nonsense with this prof. The book HE wrote has tons of mistakes in it. His class notes are very basic and unhelpful. His exams and group projects are easy but his grading makes no sense at all! (i.e. will tell students volatility is measured  percentage, then will change his mind on the final and say he wanted them in dollar figues)

He's not mean or scary... his midterms and finals are. This class WILL murder you GPA. Great person and humor but this is a tough class and he DOES NOT make it any easier. Focus on the homework and DGD exercises. Practice them A LOT. Oh! also, go to class !
He expects a lot from his students but if you attend lectures and work hard you will succeed.  He rewards students who really put in the effort.  He is not easy to contact outside of class hours.

le prof explique bien en classe mais il explique de la matière qui n'est pas a l'éxamen. il explique de la théorie vag au lieu de faire des exercices avec les élèves. Aussi quand on va le voir pour avoir de l'aide il fait le strict minimum et n'aime pas se faire déranger, à l'examen finale on a eu droit a des surprises et il été en vacances.
Great teacher one of the best that i've had. Finance can be easy if you actually go to class and do the assignment. Everything on the exams were part of the assignments. Good Luck!!

He is a nice guy but if you don't go to class, you're most probably gonna fail it; which is fair I guess. What's really annoying is that you really have to write down EVERYTHING he says. He does NOT make it clear that these little things are important, but believe me, they are. Take the class in English.
Amazing prof.  Extremely helpful, explains very well.  I have nothing bad to say about him!

Le cours de finance a ete dure. Le prof lui meme est interessant, mais na pas de slide et s'attend a ce qu'on ecrit tout ce qui dit. En finance, il faut faire beaucoup d'exemple et de repetition, mais le prof refuse d'offrir des exercise. On ne pouvait que refaire les quiz et les questions vue en classe. MAIS, le cours est facile

Le prof est super, sauf qu'il ne faut jamais être absent! Ce qui compte pour les devoirs et exams, ce sont les notes de cours. Sans notes de cours, c'est difficile de rattraper la matière avec le livre. Le prof dit ce qu'il va y avoir dans l'examen, so yé fair.  Très intéressant, un vrai "prof", il sait bien enseigner
Excellent professor.
Exam et devoir ne reflète pas le cours ni le livre.

C'est un prof à tempérament variable qui s'attarde à n'importe quoi... Attends-toi à recevoir un discours sur la follie des étudiants à chaque cours. Les cours terminent toujours plus tard que la norme et il sait qui tu es, même si tu ne participes pas dans son cours.
Best professor I've ever had
un prof imcompétent qui répond jamais aux questions des étudiants ni aux courriels, il se prends pr le nombril de la terre....calme toi bonhomme et fais ta job comme les gens !!!!!!!!!!!
Mr Chkir was a total disapointment. Without a good textbook he would be sinking faster than the Titanic. You can see he enjoys what he's doing BUT obviously it's not teaching: FAILED
Has good knowledge and a good teaching method.
One of the best. Knows what he is doing. Knows are to communicate what his knowledge. His classes are "almost perfect".
No Comments
Soooo boring... don't ask questions, you'll never have the answer you expected ! He thinks he knows everything...
Teacher has alot of knowledge in this feild
